Regression test for remap variable injection/retrieval and scoping:
 (1) a variable injected in a prolog is visible in the NGC procedure, and a change
     made in the NGC procedure is visible back in the epilog;
 (2) variables injected in a remap are deleted at the end of that remap (not
     visible in a sibling remap), including for several remaps in one block.

Re-expressed for gomc: the classic test used Python prologs/epilogs.  gomc removed
the embedded Python interpreter, so the M405/M406/M407 handlers are C interp_ext
prolog/epilog handlers (cmod test_var_inject) using the interp_ctx set_param /
get_param accessors.  prologNNN injects #<fooNNN>=42, rmNNN.ngc asserts it is 42
(and that sibling remaps' vars are not visible), bumps it to 43, and epilogNNN
requires #<fooNNN> to be 43.  checkresult confirms every prolog/epilog fired with
the expected values and no abort/error occurred.
